WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:17.000
Gordo, you expressed interest at one time in unidentified flying objects, the feeling that there might be something to all these stories. Do you still feel that way?

00:17.000 --> 00:25.000
Well, I feel that there have been a large number of fairly well qualified, or exceptionally well qualified I should say,

00:25.000 --> 00:34.000
people who have seen objects that have not had any really logical explanation other than this.

00:34.000 --> 00:40.000
I think that maybe in fact each and every one of them does have an explanation.

00:40.000 --> 00:52.000
But I think that there are so many possibilities, so many thousands of possibilities of other planets out somewhere in the universe that would have a livable atmosphere

00:52.000 --> 01:01.000
that I would hate to rule out the possibility that maybe there are people or some type of human life on some of these.

01:01.000 --> 01:10.000
And if this is the case, then it's not too unfeasible to think that perhaps some of these objects might have been something of this type.

01:10.000 --> 01:23.000
You don't think that the comparatively short step out into space that the Mercury flight will take you on is far enough out to make any observations in this area?

01:23.000 --> 01:36.000
No, I think we're still at a fairly low order of getting out into space when you regard, when you speak of space and being millions of miles involved.

01:36.000 --> 01:39.000
We're only getting out a hundred miles or so.

01:39.000 --> 01:46.000
What about the so-called Glenn effect, Gordo, the snowflakes, the fireflies?

01:46.000 --> 01:53.000
Now both Shira and Carpenter seem to feel that it's frost of some nature off of the capsule,

01:53.000 --> 02:00.000
but apparently Glenn still sort of cast doubt on that theory.

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
Thank you.

